                            <comment id="15561583" author="srowen" created="Mon, 10 Oct 2016 07:55:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, I don&apos;t see why it&apos;s valid to catch EOFException. It already returns false to signal EOF. An exception would mean it internally didn&apos;t expect EOF but read to the end.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
